{"id":481357154,"lang":"python3","time":"2 months, 4 weeks","timestamp":1618578195,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"68 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/481357154/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"14.2 MB","code":"# Definition for singly-linked list.\nfrom collections import deque\n\nclass ListNode:\n    def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n        self.val = val\n        self.next = next\n\nclass Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:\n        queue1, queue2 = deque([]), deque([])\n        cur = l1\n        while cur:\n            queue1.append(cur.val)\n            cur = cur.next\n        cur = l2\n        while cur:\n            queue2.append(cur.val)\n            cur = cur.next\n        \n        vals = []\n        while (queue1 or queue2):\n            v1, v2 = 0, 0\n            if queue1:\n                v1 = queue1.popleft()\n            if queue2:\n                v2 = queue2.popleft()\n            vals.append(v1 + v2)\n\n        N = len(vals)\n        for i in range(N):\n            if i == N - 1:\n                if 10 <= vals[i]:\n                    vals[i] = vals[i] % 10\n                    vals.append(1)\n            else:\n                if 10 <= vals[i]:\n                    vals[i] = vals[i] % 10\n                    vals[i+1] += 1\n        \n        head = ListNode(vals[0])\n        cur = head\n        for i, v in enumerate(vals):\n            if i == 0:\n                continue\n            cur.next = ListNode(v)\n            cur = cur.next\n        return head\n\n\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers"}
